update post caches "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
==================================================================

NAME
----

update post caches - Call major cache updating functions for list of Post objects

SYNOPSIS
--------

Call major cache updating functions for list of Post objects

-   @package WordPress
-   @subpackage Cache

SINCE
-----

1.5.0

USES
----

-   [\$wpdb](/index.php?title=$wpdb&action=edit&redlink=1 "$wpdb (page does not exist)")
-   [Function\_Reference/update\_post\_cache](/Function_Reference/update_post_cache "Function Reference/update post cache")
-   [Function\_Reference/update\_object\_term\_cache](/index.php?title=Function_Reference/update_object_term_cache&action=edit&redlink=1 "Function Reference/update object term cache (page does not exist)")
-   [Function\_Reference/update\_postmeta\_cache](/index.php?title=Function_Reference/update_postmeta_cache&action=edit&redlink=1 "Function Reference/update postmeta cache (page does not exist)")

PARAMS
------

-   array \$posts Array of Post objects
-   string \$post\_type The post type of the posts in \$posts. Default
    is 'post'.
-   bool \$update\_term\_cache Whether to update the term cache. Default
    is true.
-   bool \$update\_meta\_cache Whether to update the meta cache. Default
    is true.

SOURCE
------

`update_post_caches()` is located in `wp-includes/post.php`.

